name: Massage With Simon
metadata: {'@context': 'http://schema.org', '@type': 'LocalBusiness', 'name': 'Massage With Simon', 'description': 'The two types of massage I do are sports/deep tissue and relaxation/classical. I have been working as a massage therapist since 2014, in gyms, spas and as a freelancer. I studied Remedial Massage and Relaxation Massage in Australia. I have a Bachelor of Science, and a Grad Dip in Psychology. Before each session, we do a quick check in, to see what areas you would like to have worked on, and what level of physical intensity you would like for today. During the session, I will check in to see that the pressure is the right amount for you. You may talk as little or as much as you like, for me I don’t mind what our conversation level is. I will mirror you, as this helps to create an experience that matches your needs. How does massage work? The most likely specific mechanism of how massage works is through touch, with strength of intensity being an individual preference. Massage has strong benefits for mental health (anxiety/depression), which supports its use as wellness, and as part of broader approach to looking after oneself.', 'address': {'@type': 'PostalAddress', 'addressLocality': 'Berlin, Germany', 'addressCountry': 'Germany', 'postalCode': '12049', 'streetAddress': 'Mahlowerstr 5'}, 'telephone': '', 'geo': {'@type': 'GeoCoordinates', 'latitude': '52.4800766', 'longitude': '13.4237456'}, 'priceRange': '-', 'image': 'https://storage.googleapis.com/download/storage/v1/b/usc-pro-uscweb-live-media/o/de-live%2Foriginal_6240x3510_03_MG_7322Edit1_1694513125338554_admin.jpg?generation=1694513125469830&alt=media'}

Before each session, we do a quick check in, to see what areas you would like to have worked on, and what level of physical intensity you would like for today. During the session, I will check in to see that the pressure is the right amount for you. You may talk as little or as much as you like, for me I don’t mind what our conversation level is. I will mirror you, as this helps to create an experience that matches your needs. How does massage work? The most likely specific mechanism of how massage works is through touch, with strength of intensity being an individual preference. Massage has strong benefits for mental health (anxiety/depression), which supports its use as wellness, and as part of broader approach to looking after oneself.

name: Merav Pilates - Heile Haus
metadata: {'@context': 'http://schema.org', '@type': 'LocalBusiness', 'name': 'Merav Pilates - Heile Haus', 'description': 'Pilates with Merav Ben Dor. Coming from a background of dance and Yoga, I fell in love with Pilates as it helped me understand my body better, improved my dancing techniques and made me stronger and longer (and if not by actual centimeters, than at least by feeling). Not any less important- Pilates helped me regaining strength after the births of my three kids. Teaching Pilates for the last 7 years increased my appreciation both of the human body and its capabilities, and of the method itself. I have witnessed bodies change through and with the help of Pilates and believe that sometimes our body is wiser than our head, and we should just follow it to its full potential. The classes suit all levels and are putting an emphasis on the connection between breathing and moving, as well as researching the work of the body as a "whole made of separate parts". Hope to see you!', 'address': {'@type': 'PostalAddress', 'addressLocality': 'Berlin, Germany', 'addressCountry': 'Germany', 'postalCode': '10999', 'streetAddress': 'Waldemarstr. 36'}, 'telephone': '+49 1573 0761074', 'geo': {'@type': 'GeoCoordinates', 'latitude': '52.5035082', 'longitude': '13.4191845'}, 'priceRange': '-', 'image': 'https://storage.googleapis.com/download/storage/v1/b/usc-pro-uscweb-live-media/o/de-live%2Foriginal_2448x1377_merav_1583424265762472_admin.jpg?alt=media'}
description: Pilates with Merav Ben Dor. Coming from a background of dance and Yoga, I fell in love with Pilates as it helped me understand my body better, improved my dancing techniques and made me stronger and longer (and if not by actual centimeters, than at least by feeling). Not any less important- Pilates helped me regaining strength after the births of my three kids. Teaching Pilates for the last 7 years increased my appreciation both of the human body and its capabilities, and of the method itself. I have witnessed bodies change through and with the help of Pilates and believe that sometimes our body is wiser than our head, and we should just follow it to its full potential. The classes suit all levels and are putting an emphasis on the connection between breathing and moving, as well as researching the work of the body as a "whole made of separate parts". Hope to see you!

metadata: {'@context': 'http://schema.org', '@type': 'LocalBusiness', 'name': 'Mindful Body | SOUND BATH', 'description': 'Mindful Body by Xica Lisboa • Combining mindfulness with bodywork, body movement and sound I offer massages, stretching & movement classes and gong baths. description: Mindful Body by Xica Lisboa • Combining mindfulness with bodywork, body movement and sound I offer massages, stretching & movement classes and gong baths. You can find all my offers here: https://linktr.ee/xicalisboa Massages • Here via UrbanSportsClub you can book a holistic massage of 30min included in your membership, which can be also extended to 60 (+35€) or to 90 minutes (+45€) - highly recommended for an actual complete treatment. Traditional Thai Massage is the main technique used in this massage. Massages are done with clothes on and include acupressure, manual handling and stretches. Expect to be welcomed in a calm caring energy into a safe space to surrender. The Thai Massage is ended with a soft Craniosacral Touch, which relieves tension in the central nervous system, promoting a feeling of deep relaxation and well-being. You might fall asleep in the end. Testimonial • “This was the most relaxing and wholesome massage I have ever received! It gave me tingles in the head/neck/back area for 90mins straight, bringing me to a whole new level of relaxation that I havent experienced before. The massage was both comforting and medicinal at the same time, because she also helped me heal some parts that I experienced pain before the appointment. She really knows what she is doing.” Find more testimonials here: https://tinyurl.com/mindful-body

name: Modern Zouk - La Catedral
metadata: {'@context': 'http://schema.org', '@type': 'LocalBusiness', 'name': 'Modern Zouk - La Catedral', 'description': 'Brasilianischer Zouk, kurz Zouk, ist ein moderner Paartanz, der weltweit ähnlich wie Salsa, Bachata, Kizomba oder Tango praktiziert wird. Zouk zeichnet sich insbesondere durch fließende, wellenartige und kreisende Bewegungen aus, bei denen charakteristisch auch die Achse der Wirbelsäule, ähnlich wie im Modern oder Contemporary Dance verändert wird. In der hier praktizierten und unterrichteten Form geht es neben den traditionellen technischen Elementen und Bewegungsabfolgen insbesondere auch um die Verbindung und Kommunikation zwischen den Tanzenden (Paarkommunikation). Wir bedienen uns dazu an Prinzipen und Übungen von Atem- und Körperarbeit (Body Work), Body-Mind Ansätzen, Bewegungsfluss und Kampfkünsten. Der Paartanz gleicht dabei einer Konversation und die Bewegungen sind das natürliche Ergebnis eines Dialogs auf Basis biomechanischer Prinzipien. Zouk wird zu moderner Musik getanzt, von Pop, R&B, elektronischer Musik, AfroBeats bis hin zu lateinamerikanischen, lusophonen und arabischen Klängen ist das Spektrum denkbar breit.', 'address': {'@type': 'PostalAddress', 'addressLocality': 'Berlin, Germany', 'addressCountry': 'Germany', 'postalCode': '10585', 'streetAddress': 'Kaiser-Friedrich-Straße 87'}, 'telephone': '', 'geo': {'@type': 'GeoCoordinates', 'latitude': '52.5142321', 'longitude': '13.30144'}, 'priceRange': '-', 'image': 'https://storage.googleapis.com/download/storage/v1/b/usc-pro-uscweb-live-media/o/venues%2Foriginal_1024x576_sygkxcbd8mj0j1tlscmq_1735994721385570.png?generation=1751993171701706&alt=media'}

Zouk zeichnet sich insbesondere durch fließende, wellenartige und kreisende Bewegungen aus, bei denen charakteristisch auch die Achse der Wirbelsäule, ähnlich wie im Modern oder Contemporary Dance verändert wird. In der hier praktizierten und unterrichteten Form geht es neben den traditionellen technischen Elementen und Bewegungsabfolgen insbesondere auch um die Verbindung und Kommunikation zwischen den Tanzenden (Paarkommunikation). Wir bedienen uns dazu an Prinzipen und Übungen von Atem- und Körperarbeit (Body Work), Body-Mind Ansätzen, Bewegungsfluss und Kampfkünsten. Der Paartanz gleicht dabei einer Konversation und die Bewegungen sind das natürliche Ergebnis eines Dialogs auf Basis biomechanischer Prinzipien. Zouk wird zu moderner Musik getanzt, von Pop, R&B, elektronischer Musik, AfroBeats bis hin zu lateinamerikanischen, lusophonen und arabischen Klängen ist das Spektrum denkbar breit.

name: Movement Meditation with Tamara @Optionsraum
metadata: {'@context': 'http://schema.org', '@type': 'LocalBusiness', 'name': 'Movement Meditation with Tamara @Optionsraum', 'description': 'Here in Optionsraum, a very spacious and bright studio located right on the SPRE River you can experience yourself in Open Floor Movement Meditation. OPEN FLOOR is a somatic and movement meditation practice – physical, sensual, pleasurable and rich in knowledge. It brings self-awareness, mindfulness, and purpose to life. It helps us to reconnect with the wisdom of our body and heart. It deepens the connection to yourself, your relationships and the world around you. Open Floor integrates therapeutic, creative and spiritual approaches with free movement. For who those classes are designed: for those who are thirsty to connect with oneself or others, who want to feel accepted, understood and inspired. And for those of you who want to rebuild yourself, relax, satisfy the need for flow and togetherness, to feel one’s body better and get free from the stories of your mind. What can you expect: lightness, freedom, movement, sense of refreshment. You will probably meet yourself from a new perspective. Maybe you will appreciate something new in yourself. You may experience the rebuilding power of empathy for yourself and others around you, a surge of energy and an increased sense of creativity. What will you receive: You will relax and take home a sense of well-being – a better foundation, new ideas, a fresh look at yourself. Each class will give you a new resource to support you in your next week and every daily life.', 'address': {'@type': 'PostalAddress', 'addressLocality': 'Berlin, Germany', 'addressCountry': 'Germany', 'postalCode': '10179', 'streetAddress': 'Wilhelmine-Gemberg-Weg 12'}, 'telephone': '', 'geo': {'@type': 'GeoCoordinates', 'latitude': '52.5108369', 'longitude': '13.4249583'}, 'priceRange': '-', 'image': 'https://storage.googleapis.com/download/storage/v1/b/usc-pro-uscweb-live-media/o/venues%2Foriginal_2048x1152_adu7ps8niw7ujohbdn6y_1687424664919161.png?generation=1751981915835345&alt=media'}
description: Here in Optionsraum, a very spacious and bright studio located right on the SPRE River you can experience yourself in Open Floor Movement Meditation. OPEN FLOOR is a somatic and movement meditation practice – physical, sensual, pleasurable and rich in knowledge. It brings self-awareness, mindfulness, and purpose to life. It helps us to reconnect with the wisdom of our body and heart. It deepens the connection to yourself, your relationships and the world around you. Open Floor integrates therapeutic, creative and spiritual approaches with free movement. For who those classes are designed: for those who are thirsty to connect with oneself or others, who want to feel accepted, understood and inspired. And for those of you who want to rebuild yourself, relax, satisfy the need for flow and togetherness, to feel one’s body better and get free from the stories of your mind. What can you expect: lightness, freedom, movement, sense of refreshment. You will probably meet yourself from a new perspective. Maybe you will appreciate something new in yourself. You may experience the rebuilding power of empathy for yourself and others around you, a surge of energy and an increased sense of creativity. What will you receive: You will relax and take home a sense of well-being – a better foundation, new ideas, a fresh look at yourself. Each class will give you a new resource to support you in your next week and every daily life.
